    given-names: "Riya"
    affiliation: "University of Hertfordshire"
repository-code: "https://github.com/AnnyaB/Admissibility-Aware-Offline-Actor-Critic-Learning-for-Safer-ICU-Sepsis-Treatment-Decisions"
url: "https://github.com/AnnyaB/Admissibility-Aware-Offline-Actor-Critic-Learning-for-Safer-ICU-Sepsis-Treatment-Decisions"
license: "MIT"
abstract: "This repository implements LAADAN-AC, a benchmark-specific offline actor-critic method for the ICU-Sepsis Markov decision process. The project compares behaviour cloning, CQL, a vanilla offline actor-critic ablation, and LAADAN-AC using shared benchmark files, saved checkpoints, exact evaluation scripts, admissibility-aware masking, Lagrangian cost control, conservative critic regularisation, expert-policy regularisation, and action-smoothness guidance."
keywords:
  - offline reinforcement learning
  - safe reinforcement learning
  - ICU-Sepsis
  - sepsis treatment
  - actor-critic
  - admissibility masking
  - Lagrangian cost control
  - clinical decision support
